a matriarchal system any more
than we want a patriarchal

00:11:15.940 --> 00:11:16.740 align:middle line:90%
system.

00:11:16.740 --> 00:11:20.730 align:middle line:84%
Because both those words,
they imply hierarchy.

00:11:20.730 --> 00:11:22.020 align:middle line:90%
They imply domination.

00:11:22.020 --> 00:11:22.821 align:middle line:90%
>> And difference.

00:11:22.821 --> 00:11:23.620 align:middle line:90%
>> And difference.

00:11:23.620 --> 00:11:25.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Me and you, and separation.

00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:26.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:11:26.300 --> 00:11:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>> But patriarchy implies
men are in charge.

00:11:28.590 --> 00:11:30.840 align:middle line:84%
Matriarchy implies
women are in charge.

00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:34.170 align:middle line:84%
And there's something-- I mean,
we all-- most of us anyway,

00:11:34.170 --> 00:11:37.980 align:middle line:84%
grow up as children in
matriarchy, not everybody,

00:11:37.980 --> 00:11:39.960 align:middle line:90%
but generally speaking.

00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:42.520 align:middle line:90%
Our mothers run our childhood.

00:11:42.520 --> 00:11:46.410 align:middle line:84%
So we know what it feels like
to have a dominant female figure

00:11:46.410 --> 00:11:49.840 align:middle line:84%
telling us what to do
and we know how we feel,

00:11:49.840 --> 00:11:53.360 align:middle line:90%
both protected and pissed off.

00:11:53.360 --> 00:11:56.220 align:middle line:84%
So to a certain
extent, we grow up

00:11:56.220 --> 00:11:59.310 align:middle line:90%
and we rebel against matriarchy.

00:11:59.310 --> 00:12:03.100 align:middle line:84%
That's part of
human individuation.

00:12:03.100 --> 00:12:09.210 align:middle line:84%
And so when we think about
creating a new society,

00:12:09.210 --> 00:12:13.830 align:middle line:84%
I would say that it's
always in the model of what

00:12:13.830 --> 00:12:17.036 align:middle line:84%
it was like to be a child with
all-powerful parents who force

00:12:17.036 --> 00:12:18.660 align:middle line:84%
you to do things you
didn't want to do,

00:12:18.660 --> 00:12:21.030 align:middle line:84%
and our understanding
of patriarchy

00:12:21.030 --> 00:12:24.970 align:middle line:84%
is based on it being men who
make the laws and tell us

00:12:24.970 --> 00:12:25.770 align:middle line:90%
what to do.

00:12:25.770 --> 00:12:26.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:12:26.130 --> 00:12:28.460 align:middle line:84%
>> The idea of matriarchy
is based on, oh, my god,

00:12:28.460 --> 00:12:30.835 align:middle line:84%
am I going to be a child again
and my mother's bossing me

00:12:30.835 --> 00:12:32.161 align:middle line:90%
around.

00:12:32.161 --> 00:12:34.660 align:middle line:90%
And they're both kind of scary.

00:12:34.660 --> 00:12:36.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:41.970 align:middle line:84%
>> But because we're
comfortable with patriarchy,

00:12:41.970 --> 00:12:44.970 align:middle line:84%
that is with the idea of
the president being a man,

00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:47.730 align:middle line:84%
of the head of the
corporation being a man,

00:12:47.730 --> 00:12:50.250 align:middle line:84%
so many of us are not
comfortable with female

00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:51.360 align:middle line:90%
authority.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:53.790 align:middle line:84%
And so there is a
political aspect of it,

00:12:53.790 --> 00:12:59.400 align:middle line:84%
where we're now at that time
where it's been important,

00:12:59.400 --> 00:13:01.470 align:middle line:84%
and it's been going on
for the last 100 years,

00:13:01.470 --> 00:13:06.030 align:middle line:84%
where women, to agitate for
equal pay, and the right

00:13:06.030 --> 00:13:10.120 align:middle line:84%
to be in a workplace
without being sexualized,

00:13:10.120 --> 00:13:14.310 align:middle line:84%
all the different
political aspects of what

00:13:14.310 --> 00:13:16.990 align:middle line:84%
we could call gender politics
that we're working out now.

00:13:16.990 --> 00:13:17.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:13:17.790 --> 00:13:21.450 align:middle line:84%
>> But on the other hand,
we're not going to solve

00:13:21.450 --> 00:13:24.580 align:middle line:84%
the fundamental con of human
life if we just try to do it

00:13:24.580 --> 00:13:29.840 align:middle line:84%
a sociopolitical level, because
what it's really about is

00:13:29.840 --> 00:13:36.690 align:middle line:84%
the improper use of power, and
how we call that out in others,

00:13:36.690 --> 00:13:40.070 align:middle line:90%
but especially in ourselves.

00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:43.920 align:middle line:84%
And what comes to me
when I think about this

00:13:43.920 --> 00:13:46.280 align:middle line:84%
is something that
Scott Peck, who

00:13:46.280 --> 00:13:50.880 align:middle line:84%
was a very, very smart
psychotherapist, Christian,

00:13:50.880 --> 00:13:54.540 align:middle line:84%
who wrote a book called,
"People of the Lie," which

00:13:54.540 --> 00:13:55.930 align:middle line:90%
is about evil.

00:13:55.930 --> 00:13:59.670 align:middle line:84%
And he defined evil
as using your power

00:13:59.670 --> 00:14:02.310 align:middle line:84%
to avoid spiritual
growth, which I think

00:14:02.310 --> 00:14:06.720 align:middle line:84%
is the most brilliant
definition of that concept

00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:09.190 align:middle line:84%
that we call evil
as I've ever heard.

00:14:09.190 --> 00:14:13.890 align:middle line:84%
Because if you look at yourself,
at the situations in which, you

00:14:13.890 --> 00:14:15.540 align:middle line:84%
know, you've done
something unkind,

00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:18.210 align:middle line:84%
or you've pushed
somebody else around,

00:14:18.210 --> 00:14:20.430 align:middle line:84%
it's almost always
because we don't

00:14:20.430 --> 00:14:22.170 align:middle line:84%
want to admit our
own limitations

00:14:22.170 --> 00:14:23.710 align:middle line:90%
or our own vulnerability.

00:14:23.710 --> 00:14:26.310 align:middle line:84%
So we use our power to
make ourselves right

00:14:26.310 --> 00:14:27.930 align:middle line:84%
or to make ourselves
the winners.

00:14:27.930 --> 00:14:29.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Or because it's scary.

00:14:29.080 --> 00:14:30.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Or because it's so scary.

00:14:30.310 --> 00:14:31.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:31.110 --> 00:14:36.390 align:middle line:84%
>> So that's the question,
I think that yoga addresses,

00:14:36.390 --> 00:14:42.240 align:middle line:84%
that you and I are most
interested in, how do we grow

00:14:42.240 --> 00:14:45.803 align:middle line:84%
spiritually in these
challenging situations?

00:14:45.803 --> 00:14:50.940 align:middle line:84%
Because in order to right
the imbalance, each of us

00:14:50.940 --> 00:14:53.100 align:middle line:84%
has to be willing to
take responsibility

00:14:53.100 --> 00:14:56.850 align:middle line:84%
for our own
relationship with power.

00:14:56.850 --> 00:14:57.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:57.810 --> 00:14:59.650 align:middle line:90%
>> And the truth is with--

00:14:59.650 --> 00:15:02.580 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to say something that
maybe sounds fairly radical,

00:15:02.580 --> 00:15:06.600 align:middle line:84%
but women are socialized
to get approval

00:15:06.600 --> 00:15:13.380 align:middle line:84%
and to be beautiful,
to be protected,

00:15:13.380 --> 00:15:17.450 align:middle line:90%
to be alluring and attractive.

00:15:17.450 --> 00:15:21.560 align:middle line:84%
And men are socialized to
be winners and successful.

00:15:21.560 --> 00:15:24.610 align:middle line:84%
So nowadays, women are
also being socialized

00:15:24.610 --> 00:15:28.020 align:middle line:90%
to be assertive and successful.

00:15:28.020 --> 00:15:33.100 align:middle line:84%
And yet, women want to hold
on to our feminine power

00:15:33.100 --> 00:15:34.770 align:middle line:90%
of attractiveness.

00:15:34.770 --> 00:15:42.110 align:middle line:84%
So we get very mixed up about
when to yield and when to push.

00:15:42.110 --> 00:15:44.920 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, this
happens in the family,

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:46.660 align:middle line:90%
it happens in the workplace.

00:15:46.660 --> 00:15:50.980 align:middle line:84%
It happens-- it's, I think,
the source of the confusion

00:15:50.980 --> 00:15:52.520 align:middle line:90%
that women are experiencing.

00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:57.730 align:middle line:84%
And men feel that
they are not receiving

00:15:57.730 --> 00:16:00.280 align:middle line:84%
the nurturance and the space
that they need in order

00:16:00.280 --> 00:16:04.360 align:middle line:84%
to succeed, because the life
of a man in this society

00:16:04.360 --> 00:16:05.940 align:middle line:90%
is very tough.

00:16:05.940 --> 00:16:06.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:06.940 --> 00:16:09.200 align:middle line:84%
>> It's just as tough, if
not more so, than the life

00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:10.000 align:middle line:90%
of a woman.

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:12.220 align:middle line:90%
We both have our problems.

00:16:12.220 --> 00:16:15.020 align:middle line:84%
Both genders have
serious, serious things

00:16:15.020 --> 00:16:16.790 align:middle line:90%
they have to work through.

00:16:16.790 --> 00:16:20.890 align:middle line:84%
So the question really is how
can we support each other?

00:16:20.890 --> 00:16:24.760 align:middle line:84%
How can we discover
what it means

00:16:24.760 --> 00:16:27.820 align:middle line:84%
to be-- to live
with an open heart

00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:31.870 align:middle line:84%
and yet be realists about
how we live our lives?

00:16:31.870 --> 00:16:32.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:16:32.980 --> 00:16:36.990 align:middle line:84%
OK, so these are lots
of really big topics.

00:16:36.990 --> 00:16:41.050 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, we could talk
about this for probably days.

00:16:41.050 --> 00:16:44.980 align:middle line:84%
But in these confusing
times, and when

00:16:44.980 --> 00:16:47.080 align:middle line:84%
so many of these
fundamental beliefs

00:16:47.080 --> 00:16:49.840 align:middle line:84%
are starting to be reorganized
and we have the ability

00:16:49.840 --> 00:16:54.110 align:middle line:84%
to really question paradigms
we've grown up with,

00:16:54.110 --> 00:16:56.050 align:middle line:84%
socializations
we've grown up with,

00:16:56.050 --> 00:16:59.290 align:middle line:84%
structures we've
grown up with, what

00:16:59.290 --> 00:17:03.580 align:middle line:84%
are some specific things
that we can do to start to--

00:17:03.580 --> 00:17:06.670 align:middle line:84%
I like what you said about
not necessarily having

00:17:06.670 --> 00:17:10.880 align:middle line:84%
a matriarchal
leadership or culture.

00:17:10.880 --> 00:17:14.200 align:middle line:84%
But what are some things we
can actually do right now

00:17:14.200 --> 00:17:18.700 align:middle line:84%
to begin to integrate both
the matriarchal, patriarchal,

00:17:18.700 --> 00:17:22.990 align:middle line:84%
masculine and feminine
qualities into our daily life,

00:17:22.990 --> 00:17:25.970 align:middle line:84%
within us, because it
really is about us bringing

00:17:25.970 --> 00:17:30.790 align:middle line:84%
the balance and the awareness
of those energies within us

00:17:30.790 --> 00:17:33.780 align:middle line:90%
more than anything.

00:17:33.780 --> 00:17:37.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I mean, obviously, one
thing that really is important

00:17:37.060 --> 00:17:40.760 align:middle line:84%
is that we be able to talk
about difficult issues.

00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:43.210 align:middle line:84%
So the ability to
set up a conversation

00:17:43.210 --> 00:17:47.260 align:middle line:84%
and create a space for a
conversation in which nobody

00:17:47.260 --> 00:17:50.350 align:middle line:90%
is being judged for their--

00:17:50.350 --> 00:17:55.300 align:middle line:84%
let's call it politically,
socially, academically correct

00:17:55.300 --> 00:17:57.610 align:middle line:84%
perspectives, but in
which people can really

00:17:57.610 --> 00:18:01.350 align:middle line:84%
be open about where they
are, where they're confused,

00:18:01.350 --> 00:18:02.300 align:middle line:90%
is a big part of it.

00:18:02.300 --> 00:18:04.720 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's part
of what we're doing now.

00:18:04.720 --> 00:18:09.430 align:middle line:84%
But to some large
extent, it feels to me

00:18:09.430 --> 00:18:14.710 align:middle line:84%
like we need to be able to
be honest with ourselves

00:18:14.710 --> 00:18:17.320 align:middle line:84%
about our feelings
of vulnerability,

00:18:17.320 --> 00:18:20.260 align:middle line:84%
about the fact that we
don't have it together,

00:18:20.260 --> 00:18:24.530 align:middle line:84%
and we're desperately trying to
act like we have it together.

00:18:24.530 --> 00:18:30.760 align:middle line:84%
So we need to learn how to find
spaces, interior spaces, spaces

00:18:30.760 --> 00:18:34.350 align:middle line:84%
for ourselves, where we
can ask these questions.

00:18:34.350 --> 00:18:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And we need ways to hold one
another in those safe spaces.

00:18:43.750 --> 00:18:52.420 align:middle line:84%
So that a man can say, I feel
really vulnerable when I'm not

00:18:52.420 --> 00:18:55.000 align:middle line:84%
making it to the top
of my profession,

00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:58.180 align:middle line:84%
or I feel bad that
I've just lost my job

00:18:58.180 --> 00:19:00.400 align:middle line:84%
and I don't know how I'm
going to support my family.

00:19:00.400 --> 00:19:04.680 align:middle line:84%
And this goes to my
feeling of my own manhood.

00:19:04.680 --> 00:19:07.480 align:middle line:84%
And a woman needs to be
able to say, I'm aging,

00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:11.470 align:middle line:84%
and I don't feel so
pretty, and therefore, I

00:19:11.470 --> 00:19:14.020 align:middle line:90%
feel less feminine.

00:19:14.020 --> 00:19:15.850 align:middle line:84%
In other words, we
need to have space

00:19:15.850 --> 00:19:20.740 align:middle line:84%
to discuss the myths of
masculine and feminine,

00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:24.350 align:middle line:84%
and come to the place where
we can start to see, OK,

00:19:24.350 --> 00:19:27.040 align:middle line:90%
who am I as a human being?

00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:34.270 align:middle line:84%
How is my interior capacity
for nourishing others

00:19:34.270 --> 00:19:36.880 align:middle line:90%
being activated in my life?

00:19:36.880 --> 00:19:41.920 align:middle line:84%
How can I be more
assertive in the situations

00:19:41.920 --> 00:19:45.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm in, without being
overly aggressive?

00:19:45.430 --> 00:19:51.580 align:middle line:84%
How can I, as a woman, make
it clear what I want and need,

00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:53.080 align:middle line:90%
without being a nagging bitch?

00:19:53.080 --> 00:19:57.400 align:middle line:84%
And how can I as a man say,
I'm working really hard,

00:19:57.400 --> 00:20:01.090 align:middle line:84%
and I actually need support,
without coming across

00:20:01.090 --> 00:20:02.470 align:middle line:90%
as a patriarchal bastard?

00:20:02.470 --> 00:20:03.700 align:middle line:90%
So you know what I mean?

00:20:03.700 --> 00:20:07.820 align:middle line:84%
I like to some extent,
in our communication,

00:20:07.820 --> 00:20:11.500 align:middle line:84%
we need to notice our rage,
and our hurt, and our fear,

00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:13.220 align:middle line:90%
and hold space for it.

00:20:13.220 --> 00:20:16.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's a feminine quality,
that capacity to hold space.

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:20.590 align:middle line:84%
And I think that when we
talk about how the future is

00:20:20.590 --> 00:20:24.310 align:middle line:84%
feminine, I feel that
what we're really saying

00:20:24.310 --> 00:20:29.890 align:middle line:84%
is that our society needs
a capacity for holding

00:20:29.890 --> 00:20:33.760 align:middle line:84%
space for each other, for
compassion, that it needs

00:20:33.760 --> 00:20:37.070 align:middle line:90%
to be not just done by women.

00:20:37.070 --> 00:20:39.550 align:middle line:84%
The emotional labor
of holding space

00:20:39.550 --> 00:20:42.430 align:middle line:84%
needs to also be
done by both genders,

00:20:42.430 --> 00:20:44.470 align:middle line:84%
because in a certain
sense, that's

00:20:44.470 --> 00:20:48.180 align:middle line:84%
what's going to allow
new paradigms to emerge.

00:20:48.180 --> 00:20:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And so that's the way I
think the future is feminine,

00:20:52.510 --> 00:20:54.910 align:middle line:84%
by our really
understanding what it

00:20:54.910 --> 00:20:57.130 align:middle line:84%
is to be present
with each other,

00:20:57.130 --> 00:21:01.450 align:middle line:84%
to feel into presence
within ourselves,

00:21:01.450 --> 00:21:05.480 align:middle line:84%
and to connect to the
presence in us and in others.

00:21:05.480 --> 00:21:09.520 align:middle line:84%
And to do that, we actually
do need to go inside.

00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:12.790 align:middle line:84%
We need to pay
attention to our breath.

00:21:12.790 --> 00:21:18.280 align:middle line:84%
And we need to meditate,
to actually experience

00:21:18.280 --> 00:21:22.540 align:middle line:84%
our consciousness turning
backwards, feeling

00:21:22.540 --> 00:21:24.820 align:middle line:84%
into our own body,
where there is

00:21:24.820 --> 00:21:26.350 align:middle line:84%
space, where there
is compassion,

00:21:26.350 --> 00:21:27.970 align:middle line:90%
where there is kindness.

00:21:27.970 --> 00:21:35.710 align:middle line:84%
Once we're able to accept the
fact that we can bring it out

00:21:35.710 --> 00:21:36.650 align:middle line:90%
from inside.

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:37.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:21:37.450 --> 00:21:40.300 align:middle line:84%
>> And I would say
that's the feminine work.

00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:44.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, because the
feminist movement,

00:21:44.650 --> 00:21:49.330 align:middle line:84%
or I should say actually the
overemphasis on the masculine

00:21:49.330 --> 00:21:52.780 align:middle line:84%
or the patriarchy, this is
probably contentious for some

00:21:52.780 --> 00:21:55.280 align:middle line:84%
people, but it hasn't
just happened to women.

00:21:55.280 --> 00:21:56.080 align:middle line:90%
>> No, exactly.

00:21:56.080 --> 00:21:57.370 align:middle line:90%
>> It's happened to men too.

00:21:57.370 --> 00:21:58.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:21:58.170 --> 00:22:02.650 align:middle line:84%
>> And so these techniques that
we're talking about and this

00:22:02.650 --> 00:22:05.350 align:middle line:84%
ability to hold space,
and to connect with that,

00:22:05.350 --> 00:22:07.930 align:middle line:84%
and to be able to really
acknowledge what's going

00:22:07.930 --> 00:22:11.440 align:middle line:84%
on within us, is not just
something that women have

00:22:11.440 --> 00:22:15.010 align:middle line:84%
the right to do or need to
do, but also that men have

00:22:15.010 --> 00:22:18.380 align:middle line:84%
the right to do, to process,
and the need to do as well.

00:22:18.380 --> 00:22:21.010 align:middle line:84%
So when we talk about these,
it's for men, and women,

00:22:21.010 --> 00:22:23.830 align:middle line:84%
and all of the energies
working within us.

00:22:23.830 --> 00:22:29.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, and Warren
Farrell, who's a theorist--

00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:36.010 align:middle line:84%
he's a gender theorists, always
says that women have choices.

00:22:36.010 --> 00:22:39.100 align:middle line:84%
A woman can-- and this is not
true of all women, obviously,

00:22:39.100 --> 00:22:40.930 align:middle line:90%
but middle class women--

00:22:40.930 --> 00:22:43.900 align:middle line:90%
have more choices than men.

00:22:43.900 --> 00:22:47.185 align:middle line:84%
It's OK for women to take
time and work on ourselves.

00:22:47.185 --> 00:22:50.290 align:middle line:84%
It's very, very difficult
for men to do that,

00:22:50.290 --> 00:22:52.110 align:middle line:84%
because of how
men are expected--

00:22:52.110 --> 00:22:52.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Expectations.

00:22:52.910 --> 00:22:57.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, so if we could allow
men to be more like women

00:22:57.790 --> 00:23:01.390 align:middle line:84%
in that way, it would allow
women to be more like men

00:23:01.390 --> 00:23:06.070 align:middle line:84%
in ways that women need
to be more like men.

